post_text:
Board of Education Meeting - 8/26/20

Pursuant to N.J.S.A. 10:4-9.3, the Linwood Public School District will hold its Board of Education Meeting predominately virtually on Wednesday, August 26, 2020, beginning at 7:00 PM. Only members of the Board, Administration, and LEA Executive Committee may attend in person, if they so choose, subject to such conditions that the Board may set, or participate by virtual means. Members of the public will only be able to view the public portion of the meeting through Facebook feed and participate in the Public Comment portion of the meeting through a specific phone number. Directions for accessing the meeting and participating in public comment will be available on the District’s website at www.linwoodschools.org on Wednesday, August 26, 2020 at 6:30 PM.

Directions for accessing the meeting and participating in public comment will be available on the District’s website, www.linwoodschools.org, on Monday, April 27, 2020. There will not be anyone physically present in the middle school's cafetorium at the time of meeting.

BE OUR GUEST!

Beauty & the Beast Character Breakfast: Saturday, March 7th, The Doc's Place.
1st seating: 9:00-10:30
2nd seating: 10:30-12:00

All our welcome to attend the 2020 Belhaven Drama Club's Character Breakfast, featuring the cast from this year's production of Beauty & the Beast, Jr.
Enjoy a delicious brunch at The Doc's Place while Belhaven drama students perform songs from the classic musical, a preview of the April performance. Take pictures with Belle, the Beast, and all your favorite characters, while also supporting the arts at Belhaven! #WingsUp

To reserve your tickets in advance, contact Mr. Lamkin at: davidlamkin@linwoodschools.org

post_text: Ms. Bernardini's #ELA class is researching info on the book, "The Hero Two Doors Down" for Black History Month. The students are composing a five paragraph research essay about Jackie Robinson with the thesis "Jackie Robinson's strong character traits and values helped him break through the color barrier." Students will be typing their essay in Google Docs from a variety of sources such as the novel, nonfiction articles, and @Flocabulary lyrics.

SOS Group - Call to Action!
The Linwood Schools support the SOS Group and fair funding for all children in our District and the state of New Jersey. S2 is having devastating effects. Please help us to work towards a solution that will ensure that every student in New Jersey receives the education he or she so deserves. S2 as presently constructed is not the answer.

Follow this link to see how to help: http://bit.ly/2umaK5a

post_text: Fifth grade students had a great time last week on their class trip to the Philadelphia Zoo where they participated in the "UNLESS Contest". Prior to the trip, students chose an endangered animal, the Golden Lion Tamarin Monkey, and studied topics such as energy and policy change to help the animal. At the zoo, students learned from a zoo expert and saw the Golden Lion Tamarin up close. #WingsUp

post_text:
Good morning. Out of an abundance of caution, the Linwood Public Schools is going to institute a Lockout. No one will be permitted to enter or exit the buildings until further notice. There is no direct threat to the schools or any of our students. We are taking this step due to concerns in a neighboring district. Please note that we will be having Pre-K and Kindergarten dismissal as regularly scheduled. We will update everyone once the Lockout is over.

Thank you for your understanding.
